To install the e-puck compilation tools in your PC:

(1)Place compiler binaries (pic30-elf folder) into /usr/local/bin (or in /usr/bin) folder:
sudo mv pic30-elf /usr/local/bin

(2)Place epuckconnect and epuckupload into /usr/local/bin (or in /usr/bin) folder:
sudo mv EpuckSetUp/Epuck/Tools/epuckconnect /usr/local/bin
sudo mv EpuckSetUp/Epuck/Tools/epuckupload /usr/local/bin

The environment should be up and running.

Follow the examples of the labs in order to compile the e-puck library, compile the e-puck code, and flash the executable to the e-puck.
